LAGOS – An early morning accident occurred on Tuesday, around 5.20 am, at the tollgate, Sango-Ota, on the Lagos-Abeokuta Expressway. An eye witness who spoke exclusively with DAILY INDEPENDENT, said, “The accident involves an IVECO TRUCK with registration number EKY 121XH, driven by one Ariyo Akande, male, with a motor boy as an occupant, and A MACK TANKER with registration number FKJ140XL, driven by Moruff Okunola, male, who is alone in the truck. “The accident occurred when the driver of the IVECO TRUCK, coming from Lagos on its way to Ifo town, drove recklessly, making him to lose control of the truck when it entered a deep pothole and the truck tilted roughly on its side, falling on the tank of the stationary diesel loaded truck by the roadside.” EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! As a result of the accident the tank of the MACK TANKER, containing 40,000 litres of diesel became ruptured, causing the diesel fuel to start spilling on the highway, which continued until the time of sending this report. Britain’s Markets Open With Strong Lead After Brexit Deal Aide Defends Tambuwal’s Award As Special Needs People’s Most Friendly Governor At the scene to control the heavy traffic always associated with the highway are TRACE officials and the FRSC. The fire service team were also on ground to avert an inferno. Speaking also with DAILY INDEPENDENT at the scene of the accident was CDR. Ajibade Adekunle, Area Commander, TRACE, Ado Odo Ota, said, “Immediately the accident occurred, I drafted our men to the scene and also came down myself to ensure sanity is maintained and traffic is not impeded in any way. “You can see the head of the IVECO truck has been moved immediately to our yard, and the crane we earlier drafted to move the fully loaded container could not carry it, so, I have to send for another one. We had to do this t